# Using pnpm Scripts

## Dependency Management

- Always use `pnpm` instead of `npm` if possible:

```bash
# Manage dependencies
pnpm install
pnpm add <pkg>
pnpm add -D <pkg>
pnpm remove <pkg>

# List packages with newer versions available
pnpm update

# List packages with newer versions available
pnpm outdated

# List packages with newer versions available
pnpm dedupe

# Prefer over `npx` to run one-off commands without installing globally
pnpm dlx <cli>
```

- Pin critical dev tools (eslint, prettier, jest) to exact versions in `devDependencies` to avoid unexpected CI failures.

## Project Scripts

Use these commands to keep your code healthy, consistent, and secure:

### Development

- **`pnpm dev`**
  Start Storybook development server on port 6006 for component development.

- **`pnpm preview`**
  Serve examples on port 4000 using a static file server without Vite.

### Building

- **`pnpm build`**
  Build the library for production (cleans + compiles + bundles).

- **`pnpm build:lib`**
  Build only the library (TypeScript compilation + Vite bundle).

- **`pnpm build:storybook`**
  Build Storybook for static hosting.

- **`pnpm build:all`**
  Build both library and Storybook.

- **`pnpm compile`**
  Run TypeScript compiler in build mode.

- **`pnpm clean`**
  Remove all build artifacts (dist, coverage, reports, storybook-static).

### Code Quality

- **`pnpm check`**
  Run complete code quality check: typecheck + lint + format:check.

- **`pnpm typecheck`**
  Validate TypeScript types without emitting files.

- **`pnpm lint`**
  Run ESLint to catch code-style issues and potential bugs.

- **`pnpm lint:fix`**
  Auto-fix minor ESLint problems (use after quick edits).

- **`pnpm format`**
  Run Prettier to normalize code style; always after code changes.

- **`pnpm format:check`**
  Check if files are properly formatted without making changes.

### Testing

- **`pnpm test`**
  Run the test suite (currently placeholder).

- **`pnpm test:ci`**
  Run tests in CI mode (currently placeholder).

### Bundle Analysis

- **`pnpm analyze`**
  Build and open bundle analyzer to inspect package size.

- **`pnpm size`**
  Check bundle sizes against defined limits using size-limit.

### Publishing

- **`pnpm release:dry`**
  Dry run of npm publish to test package configuration.

- **`pnpm release`**
  Publish package to npm with public access.

### Hooks

- **`pnpm prepare`**
  Set up Husky git hooks (runs automatically after install).

- **`prepack`**
  Automatically runs build before packing (npm publish).

- **`prepublishOnly`**
  Runs quality checks and build before publishing.
